{"id":"elmalg-exprules_quot-001","cid":"ELMALG","topic":"Polynomials and Factoring","subtopic":"Exponent rules","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Simplify using the quotient rule: x^{m} / x^{n} (assume x is not 0)","params":{"n":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":6},"extra":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":5}},"answer_expr":"exprules_quot","steps":["Quotient rule: x^m / x^n = x^(m-n).","m = {m}, n = {n}. So x^{m} / x^{n} = x^{answer_exprules_quot}."],"tags":["elementary-algebra","exponents","quotient-rule"]}
